        <div type="letter">
            <div type="text">
                <opener>
                    <placeName><hi rend="print">Down. | Bromley. | Kent. S.E.</hi></placeName>
                    <date>Feb 9—</date>
                    <salute>My dear Sir</salute>
                </opener>
                <div type="transcription">
                     
<p>I am heartily glad for your sake &amp; my own at the sale of the book— I think you are right to publish a rather smaller 2<hi rend="superscript">nd</hi> Edit. for the public will soon find out that it is dull, though I maintain that it is valuable in a scientific point of view.<ref target="#foot.f1"/></p>
<p>I beg leave to acknowledge &amp; thank you for your bill for £300.<ref target="#foot.f2"/> Considering the great expense this seems a fair profit, but I hope it will be greater for the next edition. I have sent to Mess<hi rend="superscript">rs</hi> Clowes by today’s post a few corrections, but they will not break the pages.<ref target="#foot.f3"/> The index is admirable; by the way M<hi rend="superscript">r</hi> Dallas said to me in a letter rec<hi rend="superscript">d</hi> yesterday that he had not yet heard from you.<ref target="#foot.f4"/> If not too much trouble, I sh<hi rend="superscript">d</hi> like to hear what the corrections alone cost, so that I may hold them in terrorem over myself for my next book.<ref target="#foot.f5"/></p>
<p>Many thanks for your kind congratulations about my son.<ref target="#foot.f6"/> You know I am always greedy for presentation copies so I hope you will give me a few.</p>
<p>I am extremely pleased &amp; remain my dear Sir | yours very faithfully | Ch. Darwin</p> 
                </div>
            </div>

            
            
            
            
        </div>

        

        

        <div type="footnotes">
            <note xml:id="foot.f1">CD refers to <hi rend="italic">Variation.</hi> See <ref target="./DCP-LETT-5844.xml" resp="#mjhawkins">letter from John Murray, 6 February [1868]</ref>.</note>
            <note xml:id="foot.f2">See <ref target="./DCP-LETT-5844.xml" resp="#mjhawkins">letter from John Murray, 6 February [1868]</ref> and n. 3.</note>
            <note xml:id="foot.f3"><ref target="../nameregs/nameregs_979.xml" resp="#mjhawkins">William Clowes &amp; Sons</ref> were the printers of <hi rend="italic">Variation.</hi> CD had received a list of corrections for the book (see <ref target="./DCP-LETT-5827.xml" resp="#mjhawkins">letter from J. Daly, [before 9 February 1868]</ref>). The second printing of <ref target="../bibliographies/bibl_7951.xml" resp="#mjhawkins"><hi rend="italic">Variation</hi></ref> also contained a small amount of new material (see <ref target="../bibliographies/bibl_2662.xml" resp="#mjhawkins">Freeman 1978</ref>). CD meant that the corrections were not so extensive as to require the book to be repaginated.</note>
            <note xml:id="foot.f4"><ref target="../nameregs/nameregs_1179.xml" resp="#mjhawkins">William Sweetland Dallas</ref> compiled the index for <hi rend="italic">Variation.</hi> CD refers to the <ref target="./DCP-LETT-5847.xml" resp="#mjhawkins">letter from W. S. Dallas, 6 February 1868</ref>.</note>
            <note xml:id="foot.f5">There is an annotation at the top of the page that reads ‘corrections | £176.—’.</note>
            <note xml:id="foot.f6"><ref target="../nameregs/nameregs_1224.xml" resp="#mjhawkins">George Howard Darwin</ref>. See <ref target="./DCP-LETT-5844.xml" resp="#mjhawkins">letter from John Murray, 6 February [1868]</ref> and n. 6.</note>
